.TH SUBREG2ABRAFLEXI-INIT 1 "February 2026" "subreg2abraflexi 1.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
subreg2abraflexi-init \- Initialize AbraFlexi for Subreg integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B subreg2abraflexi-init
[\fB\-o\fR \fIoutput\fR]
[\fB\-e\fR \fIenvironment\fR]
[\fB\-\-output\fR=\fIfile\fR]
[\fB\-\-environment\fR=\fIfile\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B subreg2abraflexi-init
initializes AbraFlexi system for Subreg integration by creating required 
measurement units and address book entries. This command should be run once 
before using other Subreg2AbraFlexi tools.
.PP
The initialization process includes:
.IP \(bu 2
Creating the "ROK" (year) measurement unit if it doesn't exist
.IP \(bu 2
Creating Gransy s.r.o. entry in the address book if it doesn't exist
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR=\fIFILE\fR
Write output to FILE instead of stdout
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-environment\fR=\fIFILE\fR
Load environment variables from FILE (default: ../.env)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables are used:
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URI (e.g., https://demo.flexibee.eu:5434)
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_GRANSY_CODE
Code for Gransy in AbraFlexi address book (default: GRANSY)
.TP
.B APP_DEBUG
Enable debug output (true/false)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success
.TP
1
Error during initialization
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ../.env
Default environment file
